<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-30T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-30T23:00:00-05:00" n="573" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_EH1">Ekvall, Henry</persName>/29:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-01T12:00:00+08:00">October 1,
                                1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 1—2:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1153. [From] American Consul General at Nanking.</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“September 30, 3 p.m. Arrived after conferring with [<hi rend="italic">in?</hi>] Kuling. During the air trip to Ruling
                                September 28 I explained <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_EH1">Ekvall</persName> case to <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_STV1">T. V. Soong</persName> in detail
                                and gave him a memorandum, copy of which I am mailing to the
                                    Legation.<note n="82" xml:id="d573fn82">Not printed.</note> He
                                took up the matter with General <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CK4">Chiang</persName> the same day and
                                told me that it would not be “necessary” for me to discuss it with
                                    <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CK4">Chiang</persName> and I
                                did not. Secretary to <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_STV1">Soong</persName> told me that <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CK4">Chiang</persName> had decided to
                                send a special emissary to Sianfu to try to close up the case.”</p>
                        </quote>
                        <p>Hankow informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>